# Running fvdb_tile tests and benchmarks

When executing tests or benchmarks under `fvdb_tile/`, always use the
`fvdb_tile/run_gpu.sh` wrapper script. This sets `CUDA_HOME` and
activates the correct venv in a single command.

```bash
fvdb_tile/run_gpu.sh fvdb_tile/tests/test_hashmap.py
fvdb_tile/run_gpu.sh fvdb_tile/tests/test_cutile_hashmap.py
fvdb_tile/run_gpu.sh fvdb_tile/benchmarks/bench_gpu_hashmap.py
```

Do **not** manually `source ~/.venvs/fvdb_cutile/bin/activate` or set
`CUDA_HOME` separately. The wrapper handles both.

The wrapper is on the shell allowlist, so it runs without sandbox
restrictions and has full GPU access.
